                                <ns0:support><ns0:p>Plinth (support for a stele) with moulding around the base. The plinth is heavily damaged and all the upper portion is lost and much of the lower moulding on the sides also; the lower part of the inscribed face is preserved, marked by a number of deep striations in the surface. The plinth is the left one of a pair mounted on a single base, classified as an epitymbion of type C.</ns0:p>
